**Abstract:**
A detailed research grant proposal (CIT seminar, November 1996) examining the crisis of Catholic higher education identity. Argues that the collapse of the Thomistic synthesis of faith and reason left Catholic colleges without ideological foundation. Proposes using Henri de Lubac's contrast between Nietzsche's atheism and Kierkegaard's faith to critique Aquinas's intellectualist conception of faith as assent to revealed doctrines.

**AI Recommendation:** Important document on Catholic intellectual identity crisis; complements 96-NOV-2 and 96-NOV-3 series.

